Source: Gay New York: Gender, Urban Culture, and the Making of the Gay Male World, 1890-1940 by George Chauncey, 1994
Context: Fiorello H. La Guardia, a republican, was the 99th Mayor of New York City for three terms from 1934-1945.
Preview: La Guardia began closing Bryant Park at night in 1944 in order to “prevent undesirables from gathering.”
